    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "As a census‑designated place, Jacksonville has no formal government but is recognized for statistical purposes.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        4
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.census.gov/programs-surveys/bas/information/cdp.html"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "CDPs like Jacksonville mirror incorporated towns, providing meaningful data for unincorporated communities that lack legal boundaries.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        5,
        8
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.census.gov/programs-surveys/bas/information/cdp.html"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "Census rules require a CDP to be a single, named, contiguous area with residential, commercial, and non‑residential uses.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        11
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.census.gov/programs-surveys/bas/information/cdp.html"
    },
    {
      "id": 6,
      "text": "A CDP may cross county lines but must stay within one state, and its borders can be redrawn if the community changes.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
